<paragraph blockId="31.[811,1421,660,888]" pageId="31" pageNumber="682">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,974,660,684]" pageId="31" pageNumber="682">Identification.</emphasis>
This species is characterized by its nomadic vine life form (rigidly-scandent habit), petioles almost completely sheathed, non-cordate narrow blades with numerous primary lateral veins (nine to 16 per side). In the study area, this species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Liebm." authorityName="Liebm." class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Philodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="31" pageNumber="682" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inaequilaterum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="682">P. inaequilaterum</emphasis>
Liebm.
</taxonomicName>
due to the blade shape (see distinctive aspects in the notes for the latter species).
</paragraph>
